DataElement.preferredName: Immediate Family History Thyroid Cancer Relative Count Type
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Text that describes which and how many of the patient's first degree relatives have been diagnosed with thyroid gland cancer.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A person related by descent rather than by marriage or law._Chronological record of health and disease events of family members and ancestors. (WEBS84)._A carcinoma arising from the thyroid gland.  It is usually an adenocarcinoma and includes the following main subtypes: follicular, papillary, medullary, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic. --2003_Occurrence; an instance of something happening.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A person related by descent rather than by marriage or law.:Chronological record of health and disease events of family members and ancestors. (WEBS84)

Concepts.definition: A person related by descent rather than by marriage or law.
A record of a patient's background regarding health and disease events of blood relatives. A patient's family medical history may be important in diagnosing existing conditions.

Property.preferredDefinition: A carcinoma arising from the thyroid gland.  It is usually an adenocarcinoma and includes the following main subtypes: follicular, papillary, medullary, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic. --2003:Occurrence; an instance of something happening.

Concepts.definition: A carcinoma arising from the thyroid gland. It includes the following main subtypes: follicular, papillary, medullary, poorly differentiated, and anaplastic carcinoma.
An instance of something happening, such as an event or incident.
